README for RTAPI

RTAPI provides a uniform C API for realtime task management, shared
memory, and hardware access.  Only the POSIX/RT_PREEMPT (uspace)
implementation is supported.  RTAI and Xenomai support was removed.

Files
-----
rtapi.h                 : public RTAPI function declarations
rtapi_task.h            : struct rtapi_task and related constants
rtapi_app.h             : EXPORT_SYMBOL / module entry points
uspace_common.h         : shared code included by the launcher and ulapi
uspace_rtapi_app.c      : legacy rtapi_app process (no longer built)
uspace_rtapi_lib.c      : RTAPI library linked into liblinuxcnchal.so
uspace_ulapi.c          : user-level API (non-realtime callers)
uspace_rtapi_parport.c  : parallel port access helpers
uspace_rtapi_string.c   : kernel-style string helpers (argv_split, etc.)
rtapi_pci.c             : usermode PCI device access via libudev

Build
-----
RT module loading is now handled in-process by the Go launcher via
dlopen.  The standalone rtapi_app binary is no longer built.

The meson.build exports source/include variables for the unit-test
build only.

